HEADWORD: Candock
<hw>Can"dock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. <ets>can +
dock</ets> (the plant). Cf. G. <ets>kannenkraut</ets> horsetail, lit.
⟦ldquo⟧canweed.⟦rdquo⟧]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant or weed
that grows in rivers; a species of <gen>Equisetum</gen>; also, the
yellow frog lily (<spn>Nuphar luteum</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

